Updating Nexus Javadocs
-----------------------

1. Do a standard Maven release.

2. ./updocs.sh M.N (where M.N is the released version)

Or if you fear the shell script, do the following:

2. cd javadoc/core
3. jar xf $HOME/.m2/com/threerings/nexus/nexus-core/M.N/nexus-core-M.N-javadoc.jar
4. rm -rf META-INF
5. cd ../javadoc/server
6. jar xf $HOME/.m2/com/threerings/nexus/nexus-server/M.N/nexus-server-M.N-javadoc.jar
7. rm -rf META-INF
8. cd ..
9. git add (any newly created files)
10. cd ..
11. git commit -m "Updated docs for M.N release." javadoc
12. git push
13. git tag -a vM.N -m "Tagged docs for M.N release."
14. git push origin vM.N
